title: Frieze, 1810–20
creditline: Purchased for the Museum by the Advisory Council
description: Vertical rectangle. Neutral yellow field. Across bottom, arcade of segmental arches of varying span, outlined in black and covered with intersecting diagonal lines, and separated by green pineapples. Across top, band of acanthus leaves, alternating with lotus blossoms in darker neutral yellow. Broad and narrow black bands across top.

tombstone.epitaph:
Frieze, 1810–20.
1810–20. Block-printed on handmade paper. Purchased for the Museum by the Advisory Council. 1925-1-365.
